Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
editChangeLayer(25.10)                                  editChangeLayer(25.10)

Name
       editChangeLayer  - Changes the layer of selected wires and updates vias
       connecting to the wires that change layers

Syntax
       editChangeLayer

       [-help]

       [-layer_horizontal <layer> | -layer_horizontal_movement <integer>]

       [-layer_horizontal <layer> | -layer_vertical_movement <integer>]

       [-layer_vertical <layer> | -layer_horizontal_movement <integer>]

       [-layer_vertical <layer> | -layer_vertical_movement <integer>]

       Changes the layer of selected wires and updates vias connecting to  the
       wires that change layers.

       Note: Use the editSelect command to select the wires.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each editChangeLayer parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man editChangeLayer

       -layer_horizontal <layer>
              Specifies the new layer for the selected horizontal wires.

       -layer_horizontal_movement <integer>
              Specifies  the number by which the layer for selected horizontal
              wires should be moved. Specify a negative  number  for  downward
              movement  and a positive number for upward movement. See the ex-
              amples below.

       -layer_vertical <layer>
              Specifies the new layer for the selected vertical wires.

       -layer_vertical_movement <integer>
              Specifies the number by which the layer  for  selected  vertical
              wires  should  be  moved. Specify a negative number for downward
              movement and a positive number for upward movement. See the  ex-
              amples below.

Examples
              * The  following  command moves all selected horizontal wires to
                the METAL3 layer and all selected vertical wires to the METAL4
                layer:

                editChangeLayer   -layer_horizontal   METAL3   -layer_vertical
                METAL4

              * The following command moves all selected horizontal and verti-
                cal wires up two layers:

                editChangeLayer   -layer_horizontal_movement  2  -layer_verti-
                cal_movement 2

                So, for instance, all selected horizontal wires on M1 move  to
                M3  while  all  selected  vertical  wires on M2 move to M4, as
                shown below:

              * The following command moves all selected vertical  wires  down
                by one layer:

                editChangeLayer -layer_vertical_movement -1

                So,  for  instance,  all selected vertical wires on M2 move to
                M1, as shown below:

